To quality for Lifeline services, the income of the consumer must be 135 percent or less than the
federal Poverty Guidelines, or the subscriber (or someone in their household) participates in one of
the following programs:
SNAP;
NYS Medicaid;
Supplemental Security Income (SSI);
Federal Public Housing Assistance (FPHA); and
Veterans Pension and Survivors Benefit.

